I'm looking at my apt.conf file and have a couple of questions about the kernel package settings. 

Here are the relevant lines:

```
RPM  {
    // Leave list empty to disable
    AllowedDupPkgs {"^kernel$"; "kernel-smp"; "kernel-enterprise"; };
    HoldPkgs {"kernel-source"; "kernel-headers"; };
}
```

1. How can I configure apt to hold all kernel packages? Would using "kernel*"; be a valid syntax?

2. I'm also a bit confused about the meaning of "^kernel$"; in the AllowedDupPkgs section. Could you clarify what it does?


