Subject: Easy communication between HBs

I finally found a solution for easy communication between Handy Boards (HBs) after struggling with Randy's serialio.c for hours.  Instead, I used the Pa7_9600 Baud Serial output, which I believe originated from Fred (http://el.www.media.mit.edu/groups/el/projects/handy-board/software/serial.html).

To set this up, I modified a standard RJ11 cable by soldering the yellow Rx line and the red ground wire to the ends of a 4-pin header. One end of the header connects to digital input 9 on the transmitting HB (with the yellow end facing the LCD), and the other end plugs into the RJ11 jack on the receiving HB.

If you have any questions, please post them to the mailing list, and I'll do my best to assist. Here's a sample code example for both the transmitting and receiving HBs:

**Transmitting HB (sertest.c):**

```c
/* sertest.c: tests pa7_9600() serial output routine */
void main() {
    int i;
    while (1
